        "# Load the uploaded image from the buffer\n",
        "file_name = next(iter(uploaded))\n",
        "image = cv2.imdecode(np.frombuffer(uploaded[file_name], np.uint8), cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "U32Tmo_ECUKG"

      "execution_count": 5,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Function to preprocess the image\n",
        "def preprocess_image(image):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Apply preprocessing steps like noise reduction and normalization.\"\"\"\n",
        "    # Apply Gaussian blur to reduce noise\n",
        "    blurred = cv2.GaussianBlur(image, (5, 5), 0)\n",
        "    # Normalize the image for better contrast\n",
        "    normalized = cv2.normalize(blurred, None, 0, 255, cv2.NORM_MINMAX)\n",
        "    return normalized\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PkzunDokCbBB"
      },
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Function for edge detection\n",
        "def edge_detection(image):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Detect edges using the Canny edge detector.\"\"\"\n",
        "    edges = cv2.Canny(image, 50, 150)\n",
        "    return edges"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OuJmISicCeco"
      },
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Function for image segmentation\n",
        "def segment_image(image):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Segment the image using thresholding.\"\"\"\n",
        "    _, thresholded = cv2.threshold(image, 128, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n",
        "    return thresholded"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4kMCEiFmChQP"
      },
      "execution_count": 8,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Function to display multiple images\n",
        "def display_images(images, titles):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Display multiple images with titles.\"\"\"\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "    for i in range(len(images)):\n",
        "        plt.subplot(1, len(images), i + 1)\n",
        "        plt.imshow(images[i], cmap='gray')\n",
        "        plt.title(titles[i])\n",
        "        plt.axis('off')\n",
        "    plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3RLr7oOtCkJF"
      },
      "execution_count": 9,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Main processing\n",
        "preprocessed_image = preprocess_image(image)\n",
        "edges = edge_detection(preprocessed_image)\n",
        "segmented_image = segment_image(preprocessed_image)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dlWnCuBdCnoi"
      },
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": []
    },

        "display_images(\n",

        ")"
